---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import YouTubeEmbed from '../components/YouTubeEmbed.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Q-Tune Assembly Guide"
  description="Assembly help for the Q-Tune kit. No soldering required. Build your tuner pedal in 15–30 minutes with simple hand tools."
>
  <p>
    Welcome! You're building the standard <strong>Q-Tune</strong> kit. There's
    <strong>no soldering</strong> and no electronics experience required. Most
    builders finish in <strong>15&ndash;30 minutes</strong>. Two hex keys are
    included in the box; you'll also need a screwdriver and a wrench (some people prefer to use socket wrenches).
  </p>

  <p>
    Your kit ships with a printed step-by-step assembly guide. Follow it in order and
    keep the small hardware organized as you go.
  </p>

  <!-- Wrong kit? Jump to the Solder Kit instructions. -->
  <div class="not-prose my-6 rounded-lg border border-cream-border bg-cream-muted px-5 py-4">
    <p class="text-text-body">
      <strong class="text-text-heading">Have the Solder Kit instead?</strong>
      If your kit came with loose components you solder onto the board, you have the
      <strong>Q-Tune Solder Kit (Through-Hole)</strong>.
      <a href="/build/" class="text-amber-glow hover:text-amber-dark font-medium"><br/>
        Go to the Solder Kit build instructions &rarr;
      </a>
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>Video Walkthrough</h2>

  <p>
    Follow along with a complete, real-time build of the Q-Tune kit from start to finish.
  </p>

  <YouTubeEmbed videoId="cpOn1DBdCLg" title="Q-Tune Assembly Walkthrough" />

  <h2>Need a hand?</h2>

  <p>
    Stuck on a step, or missing a part? Join the
    <a href="https://discord.gg/evtjkEj9GX" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Q-Tune Builder's Discord</a>.
    If something was left out of your kit, fill out the
    <a href="/missing-parts/" target="_blank">Missing Parts Form</a> and we'll make it right.
  </p>
</PageLayout>
